    • Uses of Dictionary in org.icepdf.core.pobjects.acroform

      Subclasses of Dictionary in org.icepdf.core.pobjects.acroform 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AdditionalActionsDictionary
      An annotation, page object, or (beginning with PDF 1.3) interactive form field may include an entry named AA that specifies an additional-actions dictionary (PDF 1.2) that extends the set of events that can trigger the execution of an action.
      class  ButtonFieldDictionary
      The ButtonFieldDictionary contains all the dictionary entries specific to the button widget.
      class  CertSeedValueDictionary
      A certificate seed value dictionary (see Table 235) containing information about the characteristics of the certificate that shall be used when signing.
      class  ChoiceFieldDictionary
      The ChoiceFieldDictionary contains all the dictionary entries specific to the choice widget.
      class  DocMDPTransferParam
      The DocMDP transform method shall be used to detect modifications relative to a signature field that is signed by the author of a document (the person applying the first signature).
      class  FieldDictionary
      Each field in a document’s interactive form shall be defined by a field dictionary, which shall be an indirect object.
      class  FieldMDPTransferParam
      The FieldMDP transform method shall be used to detect changes to the values of a list of form fields.
      class  InteractiveForm
      An interactive form (PDF 1.2)—sometimes referred to as an AcroForm is a collection of fields for gathering information interactively from the user.
      class  LockDictionary
      The signature field lock dictionary (described in Table 233) contains field names from the signature seed value dictionary (described in Table 234) that cannot be changed through the user interface of a conforming reader.
      class  SeedValueDictionary
      The value of the SV entry in the field dictionary is a seed value dictionary whose entries (see Table 234) provide constraining information that shall be used at the time the signature is applied.
      class  SignatureDictionary
      A digital signature (PDF 1.3) may be used to authenticate the identity of a user and the document’s contents.
      class  SignatureFieldDictionary
      Signature field (PDF 1.3) is a form field that contains a digital signature (see 12.8, "Digital Signatures").
      class  SignatureReferenceDictionary
      Signature reference dictionary.
      class  TextFieldDictionary
      Text field (field type Tx) is a box or space for text fill-in data typically entered from a keyboard.
      class  UR3TransferParam
      The UR transform method shall be used to detect changes to a document that shall invalidate a usage rightssignature, which is referred to from the UR3 entry in the permissions dictionary (see 12.8.4, Permissions).
      class  VariableTextFieldDictionary
      When the contents and properties of a field are known in advance, its visual appearance can be specified by an appearance stream defined in the PDF file (see 12.5.5, "Appearance Streams," and 12.5.6.19, "Widget Annotations").

    • Uses of Dictionary in org.icepdf.core.pobjects.actions

      Subclasses of Dictionary in org.icepdf.core.pobjects.actions 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Action
      The Action class represents an Action Dictionary which defines characteristics and behavior of an action.
      class  FormAction
      Execute interface for Form actions.
      class  GoToAction
      The class GoToAction represents the Action type "GoTo".
      class  GoToRAction
      A remote go-to action is similar to an ordinary go-to action but jumps to a destination in another PDF file instead of the current file.
      class  JavaScriptAction
      Upon invocation of a JavaScript action, a conforming processor shall execute a script that is written in the JavaScript programming language.
      class  LaunchAction
      The launch action launches an applicaiton or opens or prints a document.
      class  NamedAction
      Named actions that the conformign reader shall support.
      class  ResetFormAction
      Upon invocation of a reset-form action, a conforming processor shall reset selected interactive form fields to their default values; that is, it shall set the value of the V entry in the field dictionary to that of the DV entry.
      class  SubmitFormAction
      Upon invocation of a submit-form action, a conforming processor shall transmit the names and values of selected interactive form fields to a specified uniform resource locator (URL).
      class  URIAction
      The uniform resource identifier (URI) action represents destination that is a hypertext link
      The URI can be extracted from this object so that the content can be loaded in a web browser.

      An appearance dictionary dictionary entry for N, R or D can be associated with one or more appearance streams.

      Represents a Acroform Choice widget and manages the appearance streams for the various appearance states.

      Circle annotations (PDF 1.3) shall display, respectively, a rectangle or an ellipse on the page.

      A free text annotation (PDF 1.3) displays text directly on the page.
      class  GenericAnnotation
      Generic annotation that instantiated when an annotation subtype is not recognized.
      class  InkAnnotation
      An ink annotation (PDF 1.3) represents a freehand "scribble" composed of one or more disjoint paths.
      class  LineAnnotation
      The purpose of a line annotation (PDF 1.3) is to display a single straight line on the page.
      class  LinkAnnotation
      Refer to: 8.4.5 Annotation Types
      Key Type Value Subtype name (Required) The type of annotation that this dictionary describes; must be Link for a link annotation.
      class  MarkupAnnotation
      As mentioned in 12.5.2, "Annotation Dictionaries," the meaning of an annotation’s Contents entry varies by annotation type.
      class  PopupAnnotation
      A pop-up annotation (PDF 1.3) displays text in a pop-up window for entry and editing.
      class  SignatureWidgetAnnotation
      A digital signature (PDF 1.3) may be used to authenticate the identity of a user and the document's contents.
      class  SquareAnnotation
      Square annotations (PDF 1.3) shall display, respectively, a rectangle or an ellipse on the page.
      class  TextAnnotation
      A text annotation represents a "sticky note" attached to a point in the PDF document.
      class  TextMarkupAnnotation
      Text markup annotations shall appear as highlights, underlines, strikeouts (all PDF 1.3), or jagged ("squiggly") underlines (PDF 1.4) in the text of a document.
      class  TextWidgetAnnotation
      Text field (field type Text) is a box or space for text fill-in data typically entered from a keyboard.
      class  WidgetAnnotation
      Interactive forms (see 12.7, "Interactive Forms") use widget annotations (PDF 1.2) to represent the appearance of fields and to manage user interactions.
